<plot>Signs of dramatic climate change are appearing along the north east coast of Greenland. Onboard the Danish navy vessel Triton scientists are researching the alternation of the icepack and the ship reaches a new furthest north for a non-icebreaker - 81'10 N. The crew makes the first landing on Tobias Island and hoist the Danish flag on the small heart shaped island in the Arctic Ocean.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?363231</url></doc>
